Scrapbook contains press clippings relating to various Kootz Gallery exhibitions. Includes one-man shows of: Andre Racz; Carl Holty; Byron Browne; Adolph Gottlieb; Romare Bearden; William Baziotes; and Robert Motherwell. Also group exhibitions titled: In the sun; Homage to Jazz; and Still Life. And one exhibit at the Galerie Maeght in Paris which featured several Kootz-represented painters titled Introduction a la peinture moderne Americain.
Many loose magazine pages and clippings are tucked in the back of the book.
Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution
